{
  "texts": [
    "If we set the epsilon parameter to zero and choose a sufficiently large time horizon, the agent will follow the shortest path to the goal.",
    "Nevertheless, we prefer to keep epsilon greater than zero to avoid infinite loops, even for shorter time horizons.",
    "It is also worth noting that the baseline safety shieldwhich simply replaces an unsafe action with a stop action -is stuck indefinitely in this scenario.",
    "For the second scenario, our approach outperforms retrained Dyna-Q since it can adapt to the change of the environment faster.",
    "In this particular scenario, baseline safety shield outperforms our approach."
  ]
}